title: Oxidized backup verification
agents: cmk-agent
catalog: hw/network
license: MIT
distribution: DanielDietz-de
description:
 Verifies the complete Oxidized backup chain for devices exported by Checkmk.
 The Linux agent plug-in runs on the Oxidized host, reconciles Checkmk's existing
 Oxidized JSON export with the Oxidized node API, verifies that a non-empty
 configuration blob exists in the local Git repository, and checks that the
 local repository HEAD matches the configured remote branch.

 The agent plug-in emits one central section on the Oxidized host and one
 piggyback section for every device in the Checkmk export. Persistent collection
 timestamps are maintained through the supplied Oxidized exec-hook mode so that
 a restart of the Oxidized process does not reset backup history to "never".

 Remote Git synchronization is reported only on the central Oxidized host to
 prevent one shared Git outage from creating an alert on every network device.
inventory:
 On every exported device, discovers "Oxidized backup". On the Oxidized host,
 discovers "Oxidized backup inventory", "Oxidized Git repository", and
 "Oxidized Git remote synchronization".
